parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
and the ABS system engages unnecessarily.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall or shut down while driving, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts down while driving
the vehicle loses power steering and brakes
the engine may restart after a few minutes
the "reduced engine power" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine knocking or ticking can lead to premature engine wear and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in costly repairs or even accidents.
symptoms: A loud knocking or ticking sound is heard when the engine is started
the sound is worse in cold weather
the sound lasts for a few minutes after startup.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause exhaust leaks, which can lead to decreased engine performance, reduced fuel efficiency, and potentially cause accidents due to decreased visibility.
symptoms: broken bolts on the exhaust manifold
